ARMED thugs in a grey Nissan Pathfinder SUV, blew up a cash-in-transit van on the N14 Eeufees off-ramp in Pretoria. According to cops the suspects made off with an undisclosed amount of money. It’s reported, that an unconfirmed number of suspects shot at the van from both sides of the road, while the Nissan Pathfinder was used to ram into the cash vehicle. “The vehicle was bombed and the suspects left with an undisclosed amount of cash,” the cops said. The suspects got away in a white Mercedes Benz and a white Audi in the direction of Johannesburg. Cops urged anyone who might have witnessed the robbery to come forward with the information that could assist in bringing the suspects to book.
Source: Daily Sun  